# Architecture Rules

## Brief introduction
Use these rules to keep module boundaries clean and predictable. New features should follow the same shape so AI output is reusable and easier to review.

- Feature-first: `lib/features/<feature>/...`
- Shared UI only in `lib/ui/components/`
- Shared non-UI helpers only in `lib/core/`
- New routes are registered in `lib/app/router.dart` using go_router
- New state logic uses Riverpod providers/notifiers; do not mix Bloc in new code
